  "mixStrategy": "This relaxation rock arrangement in Am uses three tracks that occupy distinct frequency bands to create a warm, spacious, floating quality. The BASS (Electric Bass, GM 33) anchors the sub-bass and bass region (MIDI 33-48, ~55-130Hz), playing slow, sustained root notes and fifths that outline the chord progression Am \u2192 G \u2192 F \u2192 Am \u2192 G \u2192 F \u2192 Am. Notes are long (2-4s) with gentle velocity (40-60), providing a deep, pillowy foundation. The CHORDS (Warm Pad, GM 89) fill the low-mid to mid range (MIDI 52-67, ~300Hz-1.5kHz) with sustained power chord voicings (root+5th), each held for 3-6 seconds, creating a wide harmonic bed. Velocity is soft (35-55) to keep things dreamy and non-aggressive. The MELODY (Overdriven Guitar, GM 29) floats in the high-mid/presence range (MIDI 60-76, ~1-5kHz) with slow, lyrical pentatonic phrases. Notes are medium-long (1.5-4s) with gentle velocity (40-65), using lots of space between phrases to breathe. Energy arc: Segments 1 (0-7.5s) at 0.3 \u2014 sparse entry, bass and pad only with a single melody note; Segment 2 (7.5-15s) at 0.5 \u2014 melody enters with gentle phrases; Segment 3 (15-22.5s) at 0.6 \u2014 slightly fuller, more melodic movement; Segment 4 (22.5-30s) at 0.7 \u2014 peak warmth, all tracks most active; Segment 5 (30-37.5s) at 0.6 \u2014 gentle pullback; Segment 6 (37.5-45s) at 0.4 \u2014 fade to stillness. All tracks follow the same harmonic rhythm: Am for ~4 beats, G for ~4 beats, F for ~4 beats, cycling. No drums \u2014 pure floating rock meditation. Rhythmic interlock: bass moves on chord changes, pad sustains across, melody weaves between bass movements with chord tones on downbeats.",
